---
/**
 * Interests
 * The things Alex is actually, genuinely into.
 */
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { SITE, SOCIAL } from "@/config/site-config";

const xda = SOCIAL.profiles.find((p) => p.name === "XDA Forums");
const uc = SOCIAL.profiles.find((p) => p.name === "UnknownCheats");
const steam = SOCIAL.profiles.find((p) => p.name === "Steam");
const psn = SOCIAL.profiles.find((p) => p.name === "PSN Profile");
---

<Layout
	title="Interests"
	description={`The things ${SITE.authorShort} is genuinely into. chip music, retro hardware, web craft, games, and other computer-shaped obsessions.`}>
	<article>
		<!-- prettier-ignore-start -->
		<h2>
			This is an
			<a href="https://chrisburnell.com/note/slash-interests/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
				interests page</a
			><sup><a href="https://slashpages.net/#interests" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">1</a></sup>.
		</h2>
		<!-- prettier-ignore-end -->
		<section class="mb-10">
			<p class="text-xs text-neutral-content mb-2">
				<span class="text-success font-bold">$</span>
				<span class="ml-1 text-warning">cat ~/interests.txt</span>
				<span class="blink" aria-hidden="true">_</span>
			</p>
			<h2><i class="icon-heart"></i> Things I actually light up about.</h2>
			<p>
				This is not a list of hobbies I vaguely dabble in. These are the things I return to on weekends, read about at
				odd hours, and drag into conversations whether or not they are welcome.
			</p>
			<p> Some of it overlaps with my work. Most of it started long before the work did. All of it is genuine. </p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-10">
			<p class="text-xs text-neutral-content mb-2">
				<span class="text-success font-bold">$</span>
				<span class="ml-1 text-warning">ls -la ~/interests/</span>
				<span class="blink" aria-hidden="true">_</span>
			</p>
			<h2><i class="icon-collection"></i> The list</h2>
			<div class="space-y-6 mt-4">
				<div class="border-l-2 pl-4" style="border-color: var(--color-primary);">
					<h3 class="badge badge-primary mb-2 font-bold">chip music &amp; trackers/</h3>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-2">
						Writing music on hardware that wasn't designed to be a music studio, four channels, a few kilobytes, and a
						hard limit on everything. Those constraints are the point, trackers are the tool, and that's how I got
						started.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-0 text-sm text-neutral-content">
						Armed with a spreadsheet crossed with a sequencer, I've been composing chip music since the Amiga days. You
						can hear most of it at
						<a href="https://asce1062.github.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> asce1062.github.io </a>.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="border-l-2 pl-4" style="border-color: var(--color-secondary);">
					<h3 class="badge badge-secondary mb-2 font-bold">reverse engineering/</h3>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-2">
						Not malicious. Just curious. Started with a Casio Databank when I was younger. Poking through every menu
						looking for edges. Better tools now, about the same amount of patience.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-2">
						Games are a particularly rich vein. Cheat codes, the easter eggs, debug menus left in shipping builds,
						messages buried in ROM nobody was supposed to find. Modding goes a step further. Understanding the game well
						enough to change it, add to it, or break it in interesting ways. I have spent more hours than I should admit
						in game memory and
						{
							uc && (
								<a href={uc.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
									modding communities
								</a>
							)
						}.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-2">
						Mobile hardware took this somewhere else entirely. Unlocking bootloaders, building custom kernels, porting
						AOSP to devices the manufacturer stopped caring about. It is the same instinct applied to a different
						substrate. If the vendor won't ship a security patch, build your own ROM. I published several custom Android
						builds on
						{
							xda && (
								<a href={xda.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
									XDA Forums
								</a>
							)
						}
						back when that was the only way to get a supported Android on hardware people still used every day.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="border-l-2 pl-4" style="border-color: var(--color-accent);">
					<h3 class="badge badge-accent mb-2 font-bold">web craft &amp; personal sites/</h3>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-2">
						The web is still the most open publishing platform humans have built and personal websites are the proof.
						Sites with actual opinions, personality quirks, and craft put into them. Sites where you can tell a real
						person lives there. The IndieWeb movement gets this right. Own your content, own your presence, link to
						actual humans.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-0 text-sm text-neutral-content">
						This site is my contribution. The source is
						<a href="https://github.com/asce1062/asce1062" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">public</a>. That is
						intentional. See also: <a href="/colophon">how it is built</a>.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="border-l-2 pl-4" style="border-color: var(--color-error);">
					<h3 class="badge badge-error mb-2 font-bold">security &amp; auth/</h3>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-2">
						Security is what happens when you take reverse engineering seriously and then start building things for
						other people. Understanding how things break makes you better at building things that don't. I design and
						maintain auth systems, think about threat models, and try to leave every system a little more honest about
						its attack surface than I found it.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-0 text-sm text-neutral-content">
						If you found something on this site that shouldn't be there,
						<i class="icon-bug"></i>,
						<a href="/.well-known/security.txt"> here is where to go </a>.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="border-l-2 pl-4" style="border-color: var(--color-success);">
					<h3 class="badge badge-success mb-2 font-bold">games/</h3>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-2">
						Games were the first software that made me feel like computers could be magic. Playing on the Amiga, then
						consoles, then PC. My wheelhouse is FPS, MMO, RPG, looter shooters, and auto-battlers. If there's loot and a
						progression loop, I'm probably in.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-2">
						<em>Borderlands</em> is the franchise I keep coming back to despite everything. The writing and gunplay in the
						first two games set a bar the series has struggled to clear since, but I still show up. Right now I'm putting
						time into <em>Teamfight Tactics</em> (made it to Diamond, Master next set?) and
						<em>The First Descendant</em> (free-to-play looter shooter, exceptionally well executed).
					</p>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-0 text-sm text-neutral-content">
						I make video content about games occasionally.
						<a href="https://www.youtube.com/@asce1062" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">YouTube</a>.
						{
							steam && (
								<>
									Find me on{" "}
									<a href={steam.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
										Steam
									</a>
								</>
							)
						}
						{
							psn && (
								<>
									{" "}
									and{" "}
									<a href={psn.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
										PSN
									</a>
								</>
							)
						}.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- open source -->
				<div class="border-l-2 pl-4" style="border-color: var(--color-warning);">
					<h3 class="badge badge-warning mb-2 font-bold">open source &amp; building in the open/</h3>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-2">
						Code that other people can read, use, and improve is code that outlasts its original context. I maintain a
						few small things, contribute to tools I actually use, and default to sharing over hoarding where I can.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-0 mb-0 text-sm text-neutral-content">
						Most of what I maintain is on
						<a href="https://github.com/asce1062" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> GitHub </a>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-10">
			<p class="text-xs text-neutral-content mb-2">
				<span class="text-success font-bold">$</span>
				<span class="ml-1 text-warning">cat ~/interests/music.txt</span>
				<span class="blink" aria-hidden="true">_</span>
			</p>
			<h2><i class="icon-boombox"></i> Music</h2>
			<p>
				My musical tastes are pretty broad, and I find myself hopping from genre to genre as time ticks on. One month I
				might be on an amapiano kick, the next I'll be obsessed with hip hop, and then I'll move on to drum and bass and
				jungle.
			</p>
			<p class="mb-4">In general, here are a handful of my favourite genres:</p>
			<div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<span class="text-neutral-content w-28 shrink-0 font-medium">African</span>
					<span class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Afrobeats</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Amapiano</span>
					</span>
				</div>
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<span class="text-neutral-content w-28 shrink-0 font-medium">Classical</span>
					<span class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Baroque</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Classical Era</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Romantic Era</span>
					</span>
				</div>
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<span class="text-neutral-content w-28 shrink-0 font-medium">Electronic</span>
					<span class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Chillstep</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Deep House</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Drum and Bass</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Dubstep</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">House</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Jungle</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Techno</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Trance</span>
					</span>
				</div>
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<span class="text-neutral-content w-28 shrink-0 font-medium">Hip Hop</span>
					<span class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Crunk</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Drill</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Gangsta Rap</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Grime</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Instrumental Hip Hop</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Lo-fi</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Old School Hip Hop</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Phonk</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Southern Hip Hop</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Trap</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Underground Hip Hop</span>
					</span>
				</div>
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<span class="text-neutral-content w-28 shrink-0 font-medium">Jazz</span>
					<span class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Bossa Nova</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Jazz Funk</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Jazz Fusion</span>
					</span>
				</div>
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<span class="text-neutral-content w-28 shrink-0 font-medium">Latin</span>
					<span class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Reggaeton</span>
					</span>
				</div>
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<span class="text-neutral-content w-28 shrink-0 font-medium">Metal</span>
					<span class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Heavy Metal</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Industrial Metal</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Nu Metal</span>
					</span>
				</div>
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<span class="text-neutral-content w-28 shrink-0 font-medium">Reggae</span>
					<span class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Dancehall</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Roots Reggae</span>
					</span>
				</div>
				<div class="flex gap-4">
					<span class="text-neutral-content w-28 shrink-0 font-medium">Rock</span>
					<span class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Dream Pop</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Experimental Rock</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Folk Rock</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Hard Rock</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Indie Folk</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Indie Rock</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Psychedelic Rock</span>
						<span class="badge badge-neutral badge-sm">Shoegaze</span>
					</span>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-10">
			<p class="text-xs text-neutral-content mb-2">
				<span class="text-success font-bold">$</span>
				<span class="ml-1 text-warning">cat ~/interests/misc.txt</span>
				<span class="blink" aria-hidden="true">_</span>
			</p>
			<h2><i class="icon-north-star"></i> Also in the orbit</h2>
			<p class="text-neutral-content mb-4 text-sm">
				Things I follow, read about, or get distracted by. In no particular order.
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<span class="text-warning font-bold">Technology:</span>
					<span class="text-base-content">
						I've always been a big fan of computers, gadgets, learning about tech, working on tech, talking about it,
						you name it.
					</span>
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="text-warning font-bold">Sci-Fi movies:</span>
					<span class="text-base-content">I have a list I need to publish.</span>
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="text-warning font-bold">Looper:</span>
					<span class="text-base-content">The best movie of all time.</span>
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="text-warning font-bold">Anime:</span>
					<span class="text-base-content">I have a list I need to publish.</span>
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="text-warning font-bold">Card games:</span>
					<span class="text-base-content">
						I'm particularly enjoying
						<a href="https://itsamandafullworld.odoo.com/shop/game-chafu-2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
							"Game Chafu"
						</a> by
						<a href="https://itsamandafullworld.odoo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> Manda </a>. See
						how it's played on
						<a href="https://youtu.be/4qcOspKct6Y" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> YouTube </a>.
					</span>
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="text-base-content font-bold">
						<em>Matcha ice cream </em>🤤
					</span>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<hr class="my-8 border-base-300" />

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<p class="text-xs text-neutral-content mb-2">
				<span class="text-error font-bold">$</span>
				<span class="ml-1 text-warning">exit</span>
				<span class="blink" aria-hidden="true">_</span>
			</p>
			<p>
				If something on this list overlaps with something you are into, I would genuinely like to hear about it. Email
				is the best way. Or leave something in the <a href="/guestbook">guestbook</a> if you prefer.
			</p>
			<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-4">
				<a href="/about" class="link-action no-underline">
					<i class="icon-person"></i>
					About
				</a>
				<a href="/now" class="link-action no-underline">
					<i class="icon-hourglass-split"></i>
					Now
				</a>
				<a href="/blog" class="link-action no-underline">
					<i class="icon-journal-richtext"></i>
					Blog
				</a>
				<a href="/guestbook" class="link-action no-underline">
					<i class="icon-journal-bookmark"></i>
					Guestbook
				</a>
			</div>
		</section>
	</article>
</Layout>
